21/12/2003
NEW YORK, United States -- The NGO Freedom House released its Freedom in the World 2004 report Thursday (18 December) in New York. 
It ranks Bulgaria, Croatia, Greece, Romania and Serbia-Montenegro among the "Free" countries -- the top category. 
Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Macedonia and Turkey are rated as "Partly Free". 
The report investigated protection of political rights and civil liberties in 192 countries. 
It has been published annually since 1972. 
(ANA, MIA - 19/12/03; Freedom House press release - 18/12/03)
